        <p> Unfortunately, the cell phone reception here was not very good, which was probably due to the aludach of the tree house.  But I wanted to have good reception when Steffi ends up in Manila. I was looking for a trike that brought me to the city, where I went to a supermarket first to really cool down. Steffi then also reported that she had a good flight and that everything runs smoothly. She stays in Manila tonight and tomorrow at noon she finally flies into my arms here in Dumaguete. </p>
        <p> I then made myself comfortable with a donut and a much too sweet strawberry shake (today is officially sin of sin) before I went back to the accommodation. </p>
        <p> There, there was still two directions until 9 p.m. Loud music came from speakers from the shopping mall on the other side of the street. Live music (pop and rock) came from a church behind the house. Since it was out of the question, I just decided to work a little and to lock out the background noise with my good headphones. </p>
